ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I have a good picture of the PR. Let me summarize my findings:\n\
n**What this PR does:**\n- Redesigns UI components in `apps/phaser3/src/ui/` to 
align with PRD-004\n- Updates `designs/issue-19/` with design assets\n- Modifies
`city-builder/ui/` files to remove `export default` and partially migrate to new
APIs\n- Updates documentation\n- Adds/updates tests\n\n**Key issues I\'ve found:
**\n\n1. **Blocking - Hardcoded colors in UI components (Foundation F-07 violati
on):**\n   - `UIAvatar.ts`: `#ffffff`, `0xffffff`\n   - `UIIconButton.ts`: `#fff
fff`\n   - `UIList.ts`: `#888888` (empty state)\n   - `UIProgressBar.ts`: `#ffff
ff`\n   - `UIResourceDisplay.ts`: `#ffffff`\n   - `UIText.ts`: `#ffffff`\n   - `
UITooltip.ts`: `#ffffff`, `#cccccc`\n   - `UIScrollView.ts`: `0xffffff`\n   - Th
ese violate `docs/design-docs/ui-style-guide/01-foundation.md` F-07 which says "
禁止在业务代码中直接使用魔法数字色值"\n\n2. **Major - `ToastManager.getInstance`
signature deviation from PRD-004:**\n   - PRD-004 5.11 defines: `static getInsta
nce(scene: Phaser.Scene): ToastManager`\n   - Actual code: `static getInstance(s
cene: Scene, startY?: number): ToastManager`\n   - `ProgressToast.ts` calls `Toa
stManager.getInstance(scene, this.startY)` which is not in the PRD spec\n   - Al
so, the `startY` parameter is problematic for singleton - different calls with d
ifferent `startY` will get the same instance but the startY won\'t update\n\n3. 
**Major - `UIList.ts` empty state uses hardcoded color:**\n   - `#888888` should
use `UITheme.mediumInk` or `colorToHex(UITheme.mediumInk)`\n\n4. **Major - city-
builder files still have many hardcoded colors and magic numbers:**\n   - The PR
claims to migrate city-builder files but only `TopInfoBar.ts` was partially migr
ated\n   - Many files still have `0x00aa00`, `0xff4444`, `#ff6b6b`, `#d4af37`, e
tc.\n   - PRD-004 9.2 says: "`city-builder/ui/` 中的旧组件全部迁移使用新版 `src/
ui/` 组件" - this is NOT done\n\n5. **Major - Missing Layer 2 components:**\n   
- PRD-004 requires 6 new Layer 2 components: UISlider, UIToggle, UIStepper, UIDr
opdown, UIPagination, UILoading\n   - None of these exist in the PR\n\n6. **Majo
r - Missing tests for several components:**\n   - Tests exist for: UIButton, UIP
anel, UIDialog, UIList, UIToast, UIAlert, UIAvatar, UIBadge, UIIconButton, UIRes
ourceDisplay, UISegmentedControl\n   - Missing tests for: UIIcon, UIInput, UILis
tItem, UIProgressBar, UIScrollView, UIText, UITooltip\n   - PRD-004 requires ≥ 8
0% coverage and tests for all Layer 1 components\n\n7. **Minor - `designs/` vs `
apps/` drift:**\n   - The design spec says "实现以 `apps/phaser3/src/ui/` 为准" 
which is good\n   - But tests differ between `designs/` and `apps/` (expected si
nce design tests are simplified)\n\n8. **Minor - `UIAvatar.ts` uses `setSize` wh
ich conflicts with PRD-004:**\n   - PRD-004 5.9 says `setSize(size: number): voi
d`\n   - But `docs/modules/client/ui.md` was updated to `setAvatarSize` to avoid
conflict with Phaser\n   - Need to check if `UIAvatar.ts` actually uses `setSize
` or `setAvatarSize`\n\n9. **Minor - `docs/modules/client/INDEX.md` not updated:
**\n   - PRD-004 9.3 says `docs/modules/client/INDEX.md` 中 "ui" 公共模块说明已
更新\n   - No diff found for this file\n\n10. **Minor - `UIPanel` lacks `baseSca
le` for show/hide idempotency:**\n    - The design spec and 01-foundation.md say
"构造时保存原始目标状态（originY、originScale、originAlpha）"\n    - UIPanel has
initial `setScale(0.8)` but doesn\'t save `baseScale`, so repeated show/hide cou
ld have scale drift issues\n    - Wait, actually `show()` tweens to `scale: 1` a
nd `hide()` tweens to `scale: 0.8`, so if called repeatedly it should be okay si
nce it always targets absolute values. Let me re-check...\n\nActually for UIPane
l:\n- Constructor: `this.setScale(0.8);`\n- `show()`: tweens `scale: 1` and `alp
ha: 1`\n- `hide()`: tweens `scale: 0.8` and `alpha: 0`\nThis should be idempoten
t since it targets fixed values.\n\nFor UIToast:\n- Constructor: `this.baseY = t
his.y; this.y += 20;`\n- `show()`: tweens `y: this.baseY`\n- `dismiss()`: tweens
`y: this.baseY - 10`\nThis is properly idempotent.\n\nFor UIAlert:\n- Constructo
r: `this.baseY = this.y; this.y += 20;`\n- `show()`: tweens `y: this.baseY`\n- `
hide()`: tweens `y: this.baseY - 10`\nThis is properly idempotent.\n\n11. **Mino
r - Some components still use `export default` or have naming issues:**\n    - A
ctually I checked and `apps/phaser3/src/ui/*.ts` has no `export default`\n    - 
But `city-builder/ui/*.ts` also has no `export default` anymore\n\n12. **Minor -
`UIButton.ts` `setDisabled` parameter:**\n    - PRD-004 says `setDisabled(isDisa
bled: boolean): void`\n    - Code has exactly this - good\n\n13. **Minor - `UIPr
ogressBar.ts` `tweenTo` missing?**\n    - PRD-004 5.10 requires `tweenTo(value: 
number, duration?: number): void`\n    - Need to check if it exists\n\nLet me ch
eck a couple more things before finalizing.',
    encrypted=None
)
